HEADWORD: Harquebuse
<hw>Har"que*buse</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(h⟦aum⟧r"kw⟦esl⟧*b⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Arquebus</er>.]</ety> <def>A firearm with match holder, trigger, and
tumbler, made in the second half of the 15th century. The barrel was
about forty inches long. A form of the harquebus was subsequently called
<stype>arquebus with matchlock</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
